<chapter xml:id="ch_motion" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Motion</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Your first physics topic is motion.</p>
				
		 <exercises>
    <title>Learning Outcomes for Motion</title>
    </exercises> 
		
		<p>After successful completion of this module, you will be able to: </p>
<ol>
<li>Analyze translational motion using a motion diagram.</li>
<li>Apply the particle model to analyze translational motion.</li>
<li>Define average velocity. </li>
<li>Define average acceleration.</li>
<li>Define instantaneous velocity.</li>
<li>Define instantaneous acceleration. </li>
<li>Analyze motion in a position versus time graph.</li> 
<li>Draw a correlation between motion diagrams and position versus time graphs.</li>
<li>Draw a velocity versus time and acceleration versus time graph from a position versus time graph and vice versa. </li>
<li>Determine the sign of position, velocity and acceleration within a defined coordinate system. </li>
<li>Determine position, distance, velocity and speed from graphs of position and velocity versus time. </li>
</ol>

		</introduction>
